<!DOCTYPE topic SYSTEM "html-entities.dtd">
<topic id="Directories_Used_by_product_to_Store_Settings_Caches_Plugins_and_Logs" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="helptopic.xsd" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <header >
          
      <intro>
          
          <p>Location of the IDE files depends on the operating system, and %product% version.</p>
          <p>In this section:</p>
          <tag-list of="chapter" title-source="title"/>
      </intro>
  </header>
    <content>
        <chapter title="Windows">
           <p>All the files are located under this directory by default:</p>
            <p>Windows Vista, 7, 8</p>
<code style="block">
&lt;SYSTEM DRIVE&gt;\Users\&lt;USER ACCOUNT NAME&gt;\.&lt;PRODUCT&gt;&lt;VERSION&gt;
</code>
            <p>Windows XP</p>
<code style="block">
&lt;SYSTEM DRIVE&gt;\Documents and Settings\&lt;USER ACCOUNT NAME&gt;\.&lt;PRODUCT>&lt;VERSION&gt;
</code>
        <h3>Example</h3>
            <list>
                <li for="ij">IntelliJ IDEA 13 Ultimate Edition:<br/>
                <code style="block">
c:\Users\John\.IntelliJIdea13\
                </code>
                </li>
                <li for="ij">IntelliJ IDEA 13 Community Edition
                    <code style="block">
c:\Users\John\.IdeaIC13\
                    </code>
                </li>
                <li for="ps,ws">WebStorm 7.0, PhpStorm 7.0
                    <code style="block">
c:\Users\John\.WebIde70\
                    </code>
                </li>
                <li for="rm">RubyMine 6.0
                    <code style="block">
c:\Users\John\.RubyMine60\
                    </code>
                </li>
                <li for="py">PyCharm 3.0
                    <code style="block">
c:\Users\John\.PyCharm30\
                    </code>
                </li>
            </list>
           <!--
           <h3>Sub-directories</h3>
                <p>Under this directory you'll find the following sub-directories:</p>
                <list>
                    <li><b>config</b>: configuration (idea.config.path)</li>
                    <li><b>config\plugins</b>: plugins (idea.plugins.path)</li>
                    <li><b>system</b>: caches, local history, etc (idea.system.path)</li>
                    <li><b>system\log</b>: logs and thread dumps (idea.log.path)</li>
                </list>
                -->
                <p>Refer to the page <a href="topicId47">Project and IDE Settings</a>.</p>
        </chapter>
        <chapter title="Linux and the Other UNIX Systems" caps="aswritten">
<p>Product directory starting with dot can be found in the user home directory. The pattern is:</p>
            <code style="block">
~/.&lt;PRODUCT&gt;&lt;VERSION&gt;
            </code>
            <p>~ is an alias for the home directory, for example <code style="inline">/home/john</code>.</p>
        </chapter>
        <chapter title="MacOS" caps="aswritten">
<list>
    <li>
        <b>Configuration</b><br/>
        <code style="block">
~/Library/Preferences/&lt;PRODUCT&gt;&lt;VERSION&gt;
        </code>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Caches</b><br/>
        <code style="block">
~/Library/Caches/&lt;PRODUCT&gt;&lt;VERSION&gt;
        </code>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Plugins</b><br/>
        <code style="block">
~/Library/Application Support/&lt;PRODUCT&gt;&lt;VERSION&gt;
        </code>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Logs</b><br/>
        <code style="block">
~/Library/Logs/&lt;PRODUCT&gt;&lt;VERSION&gt;
        </code>
    </li>
</list>
            <p>where &lt;PRODUCT&gt; is <for id="rm,py,ij">%product%</for><for id="ij">(%product% Ultimate Edition),
                IdeaIC (%product% Community Edition)</for><for id="ps,ws">WebIde (WebStrom and PhpStorm use this common directory)</for>. </p>
        </chapter>
    </content>
